>From: Doug Weinrich <dwvw59(-at-)excite.com>
>Date: Tue, 4 Sep 2001 14:09:27 -0700 (PDT)
>
>It seems the screw on terminal headlight switch is the right one for
>my 59.  Now since it doesn't have terminal #57, where do I hook up the
>little parking lights to make them work?

Hook them to terminal 58.  *Not* terminal 58a, or else they will be
on the dash-light dimmer circuit!  Hooking them to 58 means they
will come on at the first click and stay on at the second click,
which isn't stock for a USA-spec Bus but it won't hurt anything.

Matt Roberds


